column11: The President's plan to beat the pandemic is working: -Daily cases down 47% -Hospitalizations down 38% in the last 6 weeks -Case rates declining in 39 states -Hospitalizations declining in 38 states And we’re down to 66 million unvaccinated people from almost 100 million in July.

In just 8 months, the economy has created almost 5M jobs — 10 times the monthly average we inherited from the previous president. That's because @POTUS has focused on the two big challenges facing our country: getting Americans vaccinated and back to work.
In celebration of Hispanic Heritage Month, Flor de Toloache visited and performed live at the White House.  Watch the full performance on YouTube:  https://t.co/TSfVpm2kHE  https://t.co/XRiWnkAOeG

Today, President Biden met with senior officials and stakeholders to discuss the collective effort to address challenges at ports across the globe and strengthen the resilience of our supply chains.  https://t.co/EJ1Hl70n7D

Together, the President's Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will set America on track to be a global leader in industry, education, climate resilience, clean energy, and more. With these investments, we can compete for and win the 21st century.

The Build Back Better Agenda will help prepare the next generation of Americans to succeed. The plan will: -Cut child poverty rates by extending the Rescue Plan's Child Tax Credit expansion  -Make higher education more affordable -Increase the maximum Pell grant by $1,500

The Build Back Better Agenda will:  -Lower child care costs -Make universal preschool a reality -Establish a national comprehensive paid family and medical leave program And more.    Americans will no longer be forced to choose between a job or caring for a loved one.

Currently, the US is losing more than $500 billion in additional economic activity per year, because American women between the ages of 25 and 54 do not participate in the labor force at the same rate as they do in Canada, Germany, or other leading economies.

In 2020, the World Economic Forum ranked the US 28th in “energy transition readiness.” The Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will put us back in a position to lead by making the largest investments in clean energy transmission and climate resilience in US history.

China currently leads the US in steel manufacturing – they produce more steel in a month than we do in a year — and they're investing 3 times as much on infrastructure.  The Infrastructure Deal will revitalize US manufacturing and invest in our roads, bridges, and rail systems.

The auto industry's future is electric. China has produced 2 times more electric vehicles (EVs) than we have. @POTUS's infrastructure bill and Build Back Better Agenda will close the gap by establishing the first national network of EV chargers and EV tax credits for consumers.

For years, the US has fallen behind other major economies in some of the most critical areas of competition. By investing in our physical infrastructure and our people, the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will set us back on track to lead the world.

Today, we're taking a #WhiteHouseDeepDive into how President Biden's Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will position the United States to outpace our global competitors and win the 21st century. THREAD:

President Biden’s Build Back Better Agenda and Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal will help us meet the moment on climate change and become a global leader in fast-growing clean energy industries, like solar and wind power.

Before @POTUS took office, jobs were down and unemployment was skyrocketing. At only 8 months into his presidency:  -The economy has created 5M jobs -Unemployment claims are down 60% -Long term unemployment has had the largest three-month decline since 1948

The US used to lead the world in access to universal education. Now, the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development ranks America 35 out of 37 major economies when it comes to investing in early childhood education.   The Build Back Better Agenda will close that gap.

This week President Biden visited a union training facility in Howell, MI, toured a Clayco construction site in Elk Grove Village, IL, and delivered remarks on our economic progress. The President also hosted bipartisan members of Congress.  https://t.co/JYCOeRfKDs

The Build Back Better Agenda will rebuild the economy to work for middle class Americans.  It won’t cost anyone making less $400K a year a single penny – it’s fully covered by ensuring the ultra-wealthy and large corporations pay their fair share.

The Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal will invest in upgrading our physical infrastructure — roads, bridges, high-speed rail — and revitalize US manufacturing in industries like auto and steel. The plan will set the US back on track to lead our competitors and win the 21st century.

The US has fallen behind its global competitors in areas like physical infrastructure and manufacturing. China produces more steel in a month than the US produces in a year, and spends 3 times what we do on infrastructure.

The Build Back Better Agenda will make universal preschool a reality, lower child care costs, and establish a national comprehensive paid family and medical leave program. Americans will no longer be forced to make an impossible choice between a job and caring for a loved one.

If US women between the ages of 25 and 54 participated in the labor force at the same rate as they do in Canada or Germany, there would be 5 million additional women in the labor force -- translating into more than $500 billion additional economic activity per year.

In a 2020 evaluation of “energy transition readiness,” the World Economic Forum ranked America behind Australia, Germany, Japan, and others.  The Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal will make the largest investments in clean energy transmission and climate resilience in US history.

China has manufactured more than twice the number of electric vehicles (EVs) as the US. President Biden’s infrastructure deal and Build Back Better Agenda will close the gap by establishing a national network of EV chargers and providing tax credits for consumers buying EVs.

For years, the US has fallen behind other major economies in some of the most critical areas to our economic competitiveness. Together, the Build Back Better Agenda and Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal will position the US to win the race for the 21st century.  THREAD:

In the last three months, the number of long term unemployed has decreased by 1.3 million — the largest three-month decline since 1948. That's a big deal.

Before the American Rescue Plan passed, the Congressional Budget Office predicted we wouldn't reach a 4.8% unemployment rate until 2023. Today, we hit 4.8%.   Since @POTUS took office, the economy has created nearly 5M jobs and unemployment claims are down 60%.

Happening Now: President Biden delivers remarks on the importance of COVID-19 vaccination requirements.   https://t.co/IZuH39HsSF
President Biden is on his way to Elk Grove Village today to visit a Clayco construction site and talk about the importance of COVID-19 vaccine requirements.  https://t.co/Vr5YkrItL0

Vaccination requirements work. They drive up vaccination rates, which makes our communities and schools safer, along with strengthening our economic recovery. Vaccine requirements are widely supported, proven successful, and quickly becoming the standard across the country.  https://t.co/qo1swxjbYg
Read the full report on vaccination requirements here:  https://t.co/Xy4YURa8Hr

The Business Roundtable—which represents more than 200 businesses that employ a total of 20 million workers— as well as some of the largest labor unions in the country, including the @NEAToday and @AFTunion, all support the President’s plan to increase vaccinations.

Thanks to these benefits, vaccination requirements are becoming the standard – and have broad public support.   More than 3,500 organizations have already stepped up to require vaccinations, and thousands more will require vaccinations in the weeks ahead.

Higher vaccination rates lead to lower COVID-19 rates and a stronger economy.    Small business employee hours grew faster and stayed higher during the rise of the Delta variant in the states that have higher working-age vaccination rates.

Increasing vaccination rates are good for the economy.   Goldman Sachs found that “an increase in vaccination and almost full vaccination at workplaces should encourage many of the 5 million workers that have left the labor force since the start of the pandemic to return.”

In late July, when the President announced the first vaccination requirement for the federal government, 95 million eligible Americans were unvaccinated. Today, thanks in part to vaccination requirements, that number has been reduced to 67 million.
Vaccination requirements have already helped cut the rate of unvaccinated Americans by one-third.

It is clear that vaccination requirements result in more people vaccinated and save lives.    Vaccination requirements have increased vaccination rates by 20+ percentage points to over 90% in many organizations.

In the fight against COVID-19, the strain on our hospital systems, our economy, and the risk to our children is too great not to use every tool available.    A new White House report explores how vaccination requirements save lives and are good for the economy.   THREAD:
It's time to rebuild our economy so it works for the middle class — and it’s time for the wealthy to pay their fair share. The Build Back Better Agenda will get it done.
BREAKING: Health officials in B.C. have introduced more restrictions for the northern part of the province in an attempt to reduce the spread of COVID-19.   https://t.co/2XQJzgOb86
Henry - “These measures are to stop transmission and save lives. We are talking about our children who are too young yet to be protected and people whose immune systems are compromised.”
Henry says they are strongly advising people who live in northern B.C. to remain within their communities.
Henry says both indoor and outdoor sports will be limited to 50% capacity and attendees must wear masks, have a COVID safety plan and must show proof of B.C. vaccine card.

Restaurants will continue to allow indoor dining with the use of this vaccine card, restricting the serving of alcohol to 10:00 p.m. Bars and nightclubs are now closed unless serving a full meal along with alcohol.
Henry says the new health orders will apply to all of Northern health with exception of Terrace, Kitimat, Haida Gwaii and the Prince Rupert area due to high levels of immunization.
Henry says worship services in Northern B.C. are limited to virtual services only. She says single person services 'where you can have quiet reflection in a religious service,' are allowed.
Henry - Organized events like weddings will require a COVID safety plan, mandatory masks for everyone and the use of the B.C. vaccine card to ensure attendees are all vaccinated.
Henry says indoor gatherings will be restricted to 5 people and outdoor gatherings limited to 25 people but only if they are all fully vaccinated.

Effective at midnight indoor and outdoor personal gatherings will be restricted to fully vaccinated people only. Henry says if you have unvaccinated people in your household you need to stay within your household only.
Provincial health officer Dr. Bonnie Henry says young people are not immune to COVID-19. She says someone in their 20's died today in Northern health.

Together, the President's Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will set America on track to be a global leader in industry, education, climate resilience, clean energy, and more. With these investments, we can compete for and win the 21st century.

The Build Back Better Agenda will help prepare the next generation of Americans to succeed. The plan will: -Cut child poverty rates by extending the Rescue Plan's Child Tax Credit expansion  -Make higher education more affordable -Increase the maximum Pell grant by $1,500

The Build Back Better Agenda will:  -Lower child care costs -Make universal preschool a reality -Establish a national comprehensive paid family and medical leave program And more.    Americans will no longer be forced to choose between a job or caring for a loved one.

The auto industry's future is electric. China has produced 2 times more electric vehicles (EVs) than we have. @POTUS's infrastructure bill and Build Back Better Agenda will close the gap by establishing the first national network of EV chargers and EV tax credits for consumers.

For years, the US has fallen behind other major economies in some of the most critical areas of competition. By investing in our physical infrastructure and our people, the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda will set us back on track to lead the world.
